// SPDX-License-Identifier: Apache-2.0 WITH LLVM-exception
//
// test/sema/width/call_expr.test — call-expression width fixture
// (T024 rollover; specs/006-m3-sema/tasks.md Phase 4a). Asserts the
// `CallExpr` for `f(0, 0)` carries a `: BitVector(N)` Type suffix
// per `emit-ast-format.contract.md` Invariant 2.
//
// **Phase 3 stub note**: Phase 3's ResolutionPass currently emits a
// 1-bit Type for CallExpr until S22 (Phase 4b T060) ties the result
// width to the func's return-value-terminal width. The CHECK
// pattern accepts any width; once Phase 4b lands the fixture
// remains green and a follow-up may tighten the assertion.

// RUN: printf 'module m {\n  func_self f(x, y);\n  reg q = f(0, 0);\n}\n' > %t.nsl
// RUN: %nslc -emit=ast %t.nsl | FileCheck %s

// CHECK: (RegDecl {{.*}}name=q
// CHECK: (CallExpr {{.*}} : BitVector({{[0-9]+}})
